From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath11k: guard CE send-completion reap against a cleared srng

When a firmware assert storms the target and recovery fails to rebuild the
copy-engine rings, ath11k_ce_cleanup_pipes() -> ath11k_ce_poll_send_completed()
-> ath11k_ce_completed_send_next() runs on a CE source srng that
hal_srng_clear() zeroed, and ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin() dereferences a NULL
tp_addr:

  Unable to handle kernel read from unreadable memory at virtual address 0
  pc : ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin+0xc [ath11k]
   ath11k_ce_cleanup_pipes

Bail out of the reap when the srng has not been rebuilt, mirroring the existing
empty-ring handling.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ce.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ce.c
@@ -473,6 +473,15 @@ static struct sk_buff *ath11k_ce_complet
 
 	spin_lock_bh(&srng->lock);
 
+	/* During a firmware crash storm ath11k_ce_cleanup_pipes() can call this on a CE srng
+	 * that hal_srng_clear() zeroed and that recovery has not rebuilt;
+	 * ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin() would deref a NULL tp_addr. Bail as for an empty ring.
+	 */
+	if (unlikely(!srng->u.src_ring.tp_addr)) {
+		skb = ERR_PTR(-EIO);
+		goto err_unlock;
+	}
+
 	ath11k_hal_srng_access_begin(ab, srng);
 
 	desc = ath11k_hal_srng_src_reap_next(ab, srng);
